func square(externalName internalName: type) -> return type {
	return internalName * internalName
}

square(externalName: 5)

-------

struct (Value type):
* Copied when passed or assigned
* Copied on write
* Functional programming
* No inheritance
* init initializes all vars
* Mutability is explicit (var vs let)
* The "go-to" data structure

class (Reference type):
* Passed via pointers
* Automatically reference counted
* Object-oriented programming
* Inheritance
* init initializes no vars
* Always mutable
* Used in specific scenarios

-------

Nested struct good for namespacing (e.g. MemoryGame.Card)